Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Four terrorists seized a helicopter on a military 
airfield at Rostov-on-Don, Russia, and on Thursday evening set 
off for Groznyy, capital of the Russian Federation's separatist 
republic of Chechnya. 
  According to preliminary information, the hijackers, who 
have 
several hostages on board, including two airmen piloting the 
helicopter, intend to go to Iran, landing at Groznyy, 
Makhachkala and Baku on the way. 
  Well-informed sources told Interfax the other hostages were 
12 schoolchildren, a woman school teacher, a bus driver and a 
military officer. 
  The terrorists, all of whom are from the Caucasus and have 
committed legal offenses in the past, released two 
schoolchildren on the airfield. [passage omitted] 

